{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fce32901-3e95-43ce-b7e9-635d99780a8d","content":"## What happened\n\n.NET 11 removed the platform DSA implementation on macOS. Apple's Security framework dropped DSA support, and .NET followed by throwing `PlatformNotSupportedException` from `DSA.Create()` on that platform. DSA has been marked obsolete since .NET 7 (`SYSLIB0030`).\n\n## How to fix it\n\n**Best option — migrate away from DSA.** DSA is cryptographically outdated; move to ECDSA or Ed25519 for new signatures.\n\n**If you must verify legacy signatures**, use a managed implementation that doesn't depend on platform crypto:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"BouncyCastle.Cryptography\" Version=\"2.*\" />\n```\n\n```csharp\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Crypto.Parameters;\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Security;\n\n// Load the public key and verify with BouncyCastle's managed DSA\nvar verifier = SignerUtilities.GetSigner(\"SHA256withDSA\");\nverifier.Init(forSigning: false, publicKeyParameters);\nverifier.BlockUpdate(message, 0, message.Length);\nbool valid = verifier.VerifySignature(signature);\n```\n\nThis runs entirely in managed code, so it works on all platforms regardless of native crypto support.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"501c6061-0c57-4960-81d6-7c6a16fe391d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET compatibility issue with DSA (Digital Signature Algorithm) on macOS after upgrading from .NET 10 to .NET 11. Let me provide what I know about this topic.\n\nIn .NET, the DSA cryptographic algorithm has been gradually deprecated. Starting with .NET 7+, there were warnings about DSA being obsolete. The key issue for macOS specifically relates to Apple's security framework:\n\nApple removed DSA support from their Security framework/CommonCrypto in newer versions of macOS. In .NET on macOS, the cryptographic implementations rely on the platform's native crypto libraries. On macOS, that's Apple's Security framework (SecKey APIs) or CommonCrypto.\n\n\nDSA was marked obsolete starting in .NET 7 with diagnostic SYSLIB0030, but the real problem emerged when Apple dropped DSA support from their crypto APIs entirely. By .NET 9, calling `DSA.Create()` on macOS throws a `PlatformNotSupportedException` since .NET relies on those native Apple APIs for cryptographic operations. and .NET followed suit by not providing a managed implementation for macOS since Apple dropped DSA from their security framework. For fixing this, the best approach is migrating to modern algorithms like RSA, ECDSA, or Ed25519, but if legacy signature verification is necessary, third-party libraries like BouncyCastle can fill the gap.","outputTokens":1135,"requestId":"0409:20BD61:6DC5E8:7E3801:6A0529F0"},"id":"e215eb7f-493e-47b2-8e9b-c24bda7853f3","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:48:57.201Z","parentId":"e2c7b66e-6af8-4d65-9457-13bdfd36c54e"}
